org.hkijena.jipipe.api

Class JIPipeProgressInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hkijena.jipipe.api.JIPipeProgressInfo

  • public class JIPipeProgressInfo
extends Object
    This object is available inside a JIPipeRunnable and contains methods to report progress, logs, and request cancellation.

      • resolve

        public JIPipeProgressInfo resolve(String logPrepend)
        Creates a sub-progress that has the same cancellation and progress, but shows the new category in front of sub-messages
        Parameters:
        logPrepend - the category
        Returns:
        progress info with the same properties as the current one, but with messages prepended

      • resolve

        public JIPipeProgressInfo resolve(String text,
                                  int index,
                                  int size)
        Creates a sub-progress that has the same cancellation and progress, but shows the new category in front of sub-messages. This is a shortcut for resolve(text + " " + (index + 1) + "/" + size)
        Parameters:
        text - the category
        index - index of the index operation
        size - size of the index operation
        Returns:
        progress info with the same properties as the current one, but with messages prepended

      • resolveAndLog

        public JIPipeProgressInfo resolveAndLog(String logPrepend)
        Applies resolve(logPrepend) and then logs an empty message
        Parameters:
        logPrepend - the category
        Returns:
        progress info with the same properties as the current one, but with messages prepended

      • resolveAndLog
